case.name: SZBQV v Minister for Immigration & Multicultural Affairs [2006] FCA 499 (5 May 2006)

citphrases.citphrase: application to review decision of refugee review tribunal

citances.sentence: I note that the application to the Federal Magistrates Court was made against a background of considerable litigation in the Federal Magistrates Court ( SZBQV v Minister for Immigration [2004] FMCA 366 and SZBQV v Minister for Immigration [2006] FMCA 157) , this Court ( SZBQV v Minister for Immigration & Multicultural Affairs [2006] FCA 499 and SZBQV v Minister for Immigration and Multicultural and Indigenous Affairs [2005] FCA 1242) and the High Court ( SZBQV v Minister for Immigration and Multicultural and Indigenous Affairs [2005] HCATrans 485 and SZBQV v Minister for Immigration and Multicultural Affairs [2006] HCATrans 638) , concerning a decision of the Refugee Review Tribunal of 12 September 2003 affirming the delegate's decision.
